ðŸ”„ Customer Churn Analysis Dashboard
A Power BI dashboard project designed to explore, understand, and reduce customer churn through data-driven insights. This analysis identifies key drivers of churn and highlights actionable business opportunities to improve customer retention.

ðŸ“‚ Dataset
Source: 02 Churn-Dataset.xlsx

Content: Includes customer demographics, service subscriptions, usage metrics, account information, and churn status.

The dataset was preprocessed and modeled in Power BI to derive meaningful visualizations and KPIs.

ðŸ“Š Key Metrics Tracked
Churn Rate (% of customers who left)

Customer Lifetime Value metrics

Service Usage & Subscription Breakdown

Monthly Charges vs. Churn Correlation

Tenure Distribution (Churned vs. Active)

Demographic Segmentation by Churn

ðŸ“ˆ Dashboard Features
Overview Page: Quick summary of churn statistics and customer counts

Churn Comparison Visuals: Compare churned vs. retained customers across services and demographics

Correlations and Drivers: Explore links between churn and features like contract type, tech support, and internet service

Interactive Filters: Segment churn by gender, senior citizen status, payment method, and more

ðŸ§  Key Insights
Customers with shorter tenure and month-to-month contracts are more likely to churn

Tech support and fiber optic users show higher churn likelihood

Customers with paperless billing and electronic payment methods churn more frequently

Multi-line service bundles help reduce churn risk

